history.content:
I'm in 186 this semester, and so far there hasn't been much of anything that requires 61C. There has been some hashing stuff, but I think you can learn it without having taken 61C, just do some practice on it. Most of the material is stuff you learned or discussed in 61B and just new stuff. I guess having taken 61C would help you to see the bigger picture in some of the topics and why certain database design choices are made, but you can probably get by without it.

I think 186 is less popular than 188, so you'll more likely have a better chance.

Thank you!
